AB  - The criminal law in a democratic state has the essential function of protecting legal interests to the community. The right to an ecologically balanced environment was a choice of the original constituent power, which now provides for penalties for violators and the legal environment and that, in criminal terms, were regulated with the enactment of Law n. 9.605/1998. This Act provides, in article 48, the environmental protection hamper the natural regeneration of forests and other forms of vegetation, this being a permanent offense, since its consummation protrudes in time. Thus, in the case of permanent crime, includes conduct that began before his typing, if the violation of the environment has not yet ceased. This is the case of environmental crimes perpetrated in the 1970s, with the implementation of Forest Districts in northern Minas Gerais and in Jequitinhonha Valley.
