AB  - The new genus Arauchemus is proposed to include two new species from southern Brazil. Arauchemus graudo sp. nov. and Arauchemus miudo sp. nov. are described from Sao Francisco de Paula in the state of Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil. Both sympatric species were sampled along 20 months at three different habitats: primary and secondary forests and at Pinus silvicultures. A. graudo sp. nov. and A. miudo sp. nov. presented larger numbers at primary and secondary forests respectively. Both species presented stenochronic male activity patterns with male activity peak between the end of summer and beginning of autumn. Morphometric data on male cephalothorax indicate large size overlapping of both species.
